      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Simmer the fruit, 5 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{raisins}}, {{sultanas}}, {{dried-currants}}, {{mixed-peel}}, {{unsalted-butter}}, {{dark-brown-sugar}}, {{water}}, and {{mixed-spice}} in a medium saucepan. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat, stirring until the butter melts and the sugar dissolves. Simmer for 5 minutes. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "boiled cake method",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yf4bi0000rsv4kl8fi59g"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": the fruit absorbs the liquid and plumps. Pour into a large bowl and leave to cool for 20 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the dry ingredients and eggs",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 160°C fan. Butter and double-line the round tin with baking paper. Once the fruit mixture has cooled to warm (not hot), stir in the beaten {{eggs}}. Add the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} and fold until fully combined.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 75 to 80 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon into the prepared tin and level the surface. Bake for 75 to 80 minutes until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean and the internal temperature reads 92°C. Lay a piece of baking paper over the top after 50 minutes if the surface is browning. Leave to cool completely in the tin before turning out. Wrap in foil and store at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
